{"article_id":"hr80FduPJmOkYkWC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The president is turning up the heat on John Boehner and Mitch McConnell .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"GOP tries to cope with tax hike reality","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"With three weeks to go","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"before the Bush tax rates expire","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"and the Pentagon and other federal agencies face tens of billions of dollars in spending cuts ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"a reality for Republicans has set in :","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Tax rates are going up ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"and the only real question is by how much and for whom .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"From Capitol Hill to K Street , many Republicans are discussing a small boost in marginal tax rates","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"that would be coupled with raising the threshold for wealthy Americans","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"facing tax increases from $ 250,000 to $ 500,000 or higher in annual income .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Of course , any rate increase for Republicans","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"- one","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that rank-and-file lawmakers could back and defend -","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"would have to come with serious cuts to entitlement programs .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"And there ' s no evidence","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"President Barack Obama and Democrats have given in on any specific entitlement cuts in closed-door negotiations","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"- especially enough","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"to offset a rate change and an increase in the threshold for the rich .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"\" Both sides have to hold hands","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and jump on this one , \"","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"said a top Senate aide .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"Yet","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"if House Speaker John Boehner","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"and Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"( R-Ky. )","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"are unable to come to an agreement with Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"the highest marginal tax rate will jump from 35 percent to 39.6 percent on Jan. 1 , the same as it was under former President Bill Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Tax rates on estates will soar ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"and nearly 30 million more Americans will get hit with the alternative minimum tax ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"originally aimed at making sure","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"wealthier individuals and families couldn ' t completely avoid federal taxes .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"There are numerous problems with the modest tax hikes for entitlement cuts trade off ,","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"which","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"GOP Hill aides stressed","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"has not been formally offered yet .","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"First , Democrats believe","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"they are dealing from a place of strength in these negotiations","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"and are unlikely to give up concessions on entitlement programs","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"without big moves by Boehner .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"\" We are winning , \"","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"said a top Hill Democratic staffer .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"\" We don ' t have to give up on anything yet . \"","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"Boehner also faces pressure from his right","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"and is concerned","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"whether House Majority Leader Eric Cantor","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"( R-Va. )","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"and Budget Committee Chairman Paul Ryan","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"( R-Wis. )","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"will support him .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"He has so far refused to agree to any increase in tax rates","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"even though many in his party are already acknowledging","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"such an outcome is unavoidable .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"The best","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Republicans can do ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"these lawmakers say ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"is limit the size of the increases","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"while working to shift the political blame to Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"\" The speaker is opposed to raising tax rates ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"because raising tax rates costs jobs , \"","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"said Michael Steel , spokesman for Boehner .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"On top of that , any suggestion","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Republicans could back a tax increase","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"faces some stiff opposition in the Senate .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"\" That doesn ' t really help solve the problem , \"","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Sen. Orrin Hatch","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"( R-Utah )","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"said","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"of increasing the tax threshold for the wealthy .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Hatch is ranking member of the powerful Finance Committee .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"\" I ' m against raising tax rates .","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"We know","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"if we raise those tax rates","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"and we don ' t have corresponding reductions in spending ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"we ' ll get the tax rates and no spending reductions .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"That ' s just a game","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"that the Democrats play over and over and over ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"and the American people let them get away with it sometimes . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":159,"left":81,"right":158,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":81,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":111,"right":157,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":111,"left":86,"right":110,"relation":"ela